This is a Full-Time position with the Department of Social Services. For more information on the Department of Social Services, please visit https://dss.sd.gov/ .

The South Dakota Department of Social Services, Division of Medical Services also knowns as South Dakota Medicaid plays a vital role in the healthcare of many South Dakotans. The program is one of the largest healthcare insurers in South Dakota, covering 143,063 individuals in state fiscal year 2021. The program primarily covers children of low - income families including approximately 50 percent of children in South Dakota under age one. Other individuals covered by South Dakota Medicaid include low-income pregnant women, parents, and other caretaker relatives, seniors in nursing homes, and individuals with physical or developmental disabilities.

The South Dakota Medicaid reimbursement strategy and analytics manager position plays an important role in helping set and implement reimbursement policies for Medicaid providers. Duties of the position include:
• managing and coordinating updates of reimbursement methodologies including annual rate updates for professional and facility services;
• researching reimbursement best practices;
• researching other payer's reimbursement policies and rates;
• drafting reimbursement policies;
• analyzing Medicaid claims data to inform reimbursement policy decisions;
• preparing Medicaid financial reports from claims data;
• calculating fiscal impacts for Medicaid initiatives using claims data and modeling analysis;
• managing Medicaid vendor contracts related to reimbursement;
• overseeing the annual Upper Payment Limit demonstration process.

Licenses and Certifications:

A bachelor's or master's degree in a relevant field is preferred.

The Ideal Candidate Will Have:
• data analytics experience and knowledge including knowledge of SQL;
• project management and leadership skills;
• experience in healthcare administration or with healthcare reimbursement methodologies including MS-DRG and APC;
• effective verbal and written communication;
• knowledge of Medicaid reimbursement methodologies.

Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:
• high attention to detail;
• research and analysis skills;
• ability to analyze and interpret data;
• leadership skills and an ability to lead organizational change;
• ability to identify, recommend, and implement process improvements and efficiencies;
• project management skills including managing multiple projects;
• ability to prepare, review, and analyze reports;
• ability to conduct strategic planning and problem solving.

Additional Requirements: To be considered, please attach your resume.

This position is exempt from the Civil Service Act.
This position is eligible for Veterans' Preference per ARSD 55:10:02:08.

NCRC: If you possess a National Career Readiness Certificate, please submit the certificate with your application. For more information on how to acquire a National Career Readiness Certificate contact a South Dakota Department of Labor and Regulation Job Service Office. A certificate is not necessary to be considered.

The State of South Dakota does not sponsor work visas for new or existing employees. All persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and complete an Employment Eligibility Verification, Form I-9. The State of South Dakota as an employer will be using E-Verify to complete employment eligibility verification upon hire.

The State of South Dakota offers employer paid health insurance plus eleven paid holidays, generous vacation and sick leave accrual, dental, vision, and other insurance options, and retirement benefits. You can view our benefits information at https://bhr.sd.gov/job-seekers/work-for-state-government/ . This position is a member of Class A retirement under SDRS.

